AAPS 4 DEV from:
7734facd Milos Kozak <m.kozak@sysop.cz> on 01.06.2026 at 23:02
Maybe newer one wont work if the linenumber changed...


Adds a small, whitelisted external entry point that lets 10BE CarbCam
(package de.be10.carbcam) open the AAPS V4 Compose Bolus Wizard with
the carbs (and optional notes) field prefilled.

Design notes:

  * Caller package is verified against a hard-coded whitelist in
    WizardLaunchActivity. Any other caller is silently rejected.
  * Carbs are bounds-checked to 1..80 g; out-of-range values are
    silently rejected. Larger meals can be adjusted manually in the
    wizard afterwards.
  * The launcher activity only forwards the value to
    ComposeMainActivity via internal Intent extras (external_carbs,
    external_notes, external_source). ComposeMainActivity routes them
    via NavController to the existing AppRoute.WizardDialog which
    already accepts carbs and notes as nav arguments (used today by
    the food management screen). The Wizard ViewModel reads these
    from SavedStateHandle and prefills the UI state.
  * All confirmation dialogs, safety checks and bolus logic remain
    completely unchanged.
  * No insulin is ever delivered without the standard wizard
    confirmation flow.

Cold-start safe: the pending carbs intent is held in a mutableStateOf
property on ComposeMainActivity, so the AppContent composable picks
it up via LaunchedEffect once the NavHostController is ready,
regardless of whether the intent arrived during cold start or while
the app was already running.

The intent extras are explicitly removed after consumption so that a
configuration change (rotation, theme change) does not re-trigger
navigation to the wizard.

Intent contract:

  action  : info.nightscout.androidaps.action.OPEN_BOLUS_WIZARD
  extras  : carbs  (int,    required, 1..80, grams)
            notes  (string, optional)
            source (string, optional, free-form caller tag)

Target branch: nightscout/AndroidAPS dev (4.x)
